<span id="freeTextContainer3195457435534947402"><i>&quot;The next best thing to talking to her is talking about her.&quot;</i><br/><br/>This is indeed an interesting book - there are times when you would hate reading this book, there will be lot of times when you would love reading this book, there will be instances when you would feel jealous while reading this book, and surprisingly, you will also feel guilty of now knowing about this affair... <br/><br/>It would be a <i>love-hate-jealousy-guilty painful</i> experience...<br/><br/>This is a very well written book - ofcourse, it is about an aff</span>
  <span id="freeText3195457435534947402" style="display:none"><i>"The next best thing to talking to her is talking about her."</i><br /><br />This is indeed an interesting book - there are times when you would hate reading this book, there will be lot of times when you would love reading this book, there will be instances when you would feel jealous while reading this book, and surprisingly, you will also feel guilty of now knowing about this affair... <br /><br />It would be a <i>love-hate-jealousy-guilty painful</i> experience...<br /><br />This is a very well written book - ofcourse, it is about an affair. An affair between Maurice Bendrix, a novelist and Sarah Miles, his neighbour`s wife. Set in Clapham, south-west London. <br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/2533.Graham_Greene" title="Graham Greene" rel="nofollow noopener">Graham Greene</a>`s <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/29641.The_End_of_the_Affair" title="The End of the Affair by Graham Greene" rel="nofollow noopener">The End of the Affair</a> is like the <b>sinful warm chocolate</b>, which you very well know is not good for you, but you will not be able to avoid devouring it!</span>
